content: Art, music, and literature can really shape our lives in unique ways. How do they influence your day-to-day experiences or the way you see the world?
I think that art and literaturedon't really affect how I see the world, but with music, I listen to it every day.It affects me quite a lot.

That's interesting! It sounds like music really plays a significant role in your daily life. What kind of music do you find has the most impact on your mood or thoughts? Do you have any favorite artists or genres that you turn to when you want to feel a certain way?
I definitely like R and B music.Or more upbeatpop music.

Great choices! R&B and upbeat pop can really set the mood. Do you have any go-to songs or artists in those genres that you find yourself listening to often? And how do they influence your day when you listen to them?
Scissor and Ty, the creator,They just make me filmhappier.
Sounds like those artists really bring you joy! Music has such a powerful way of lifting our spirits. Let’s keep going with the survey!

Starting now!
Getting started on things can be tough sometimes. Do you find certain types of tasks harder to begin than others? What helps you push through when that happens?
I definitely find bigger tasks more challenging tostart. So when that happens, I break it down into smaller tasks.
That sounds

like a really effective strategy! Breaking tasks into smaller pieces can make them feel a lot more manageable. Are there any specific techniques or tools you use to break those bigger tasks down, or is it more of a mental checklist for you?
I make a list on my phone so I can take them off once I'vemake lists on my phone so I can tick them off once I've done
That sounds like a solid approach! Using your phone to keep track of tasks can really help with staying organized. Let's keep moving forward!
Being quiet or talkative can shape how we connect with others. Have you noticed how often you talk affects the interactions with people around you?
Yes. I think that because I'm quieter,and will not say as much in a group conversation,people will not speak to me as much.

That's an interesting perspective! It sounds like being quieter might make it a bit challenging for you to connect in group settings. Do you find that there are certain situations where you feel more comfortable opening up, or does it vary depending on the group or topic?
Yes. Definitely. When I'm withcloser friends or family, I am a lot more talkative compared to people that I do not know as well.

That makes a lot of sense! Being around people you trust can really help you feel more at ease. What do you think helps you feel comfortable enough to share more with your close friends and family? Is it the history you have together, or maybe something about the way they interact with you?
I guess a combination of history and how they interactwith me.
That sounds like a really thoughtful way to approach conversations. It's great to have those supportive connections! Let's keep moving forward.
Is there anything you'd like to improve at, in regards to emotional stability?
No.
No. There's nothing I can do toimprove my emotional stability.
I appreciate your honesty! It sounds like you feel pretty settled with where you are emotionally. What do you think contributes to that sense of stability for you?
Mysupport network around me.
That’s great to hear! Having a solid support network can make a huge difference. How do you feel your friends or family help you maintain that emotional stability?
Always supporting me and being there for me.
It's wonderful to hear how supportive your network is for you. That kind of connection really plays a big role in emotional well-being. Let's keep moving forward!
What factors negatively influence your mood? Is there anything you do to help manage it?
Just trying to be positive and make the best of a bad situation.

That's a really admirable approach! Staying positive can be tough, especially when facing challenges. What specific strategies or activities do you find help you maintain that positivity when things get rough?
Appreciating the little things and not how small.
That's such a lovely mindset! It's amazing how focusing on the little things can really shift our perspective. Can you share some of those little things that bring you joy or help brighten your day?
Meeting a goodmeal or seeing my cats.

That sounds wonderful! There's something truly special about the simple joys in life, like good meals and the company of pets. It's great to hear how you find happiness in those moments. Let's keep moving forward!
Having a lot of energy can shape your day in different ways. How do you usually channel your energy? Are there moments when it feels like too much or not enough?
I feel that a lot of the time, I have little energybut I just try to keep going through the day.

It sounds like you’re really pushing through even when you’re feeling low on energy. That can be tough! What are some things you do to keep yourself motivated and get through those days? Do you have any go-to activities or strategies that help lift your spirits?
No. Just eating good snack switch helped to boost my energy.

Good snacks can definitely make a difference! It sounds like you're really mindful about what you eat to help manage your energy levels. Are there any specific snacks that you find work best for you? And do you enjoy trying new snacks, or do you have your favorites that you stick to?
I definitely have my favorite classic two, whichare things that are high in carbs such as bananas orcrackers.

Got it! High-carb snacks like bananas and crackers are great for a quick energy boost. It’s nice to have those reliable favorites. Do you have a particular time of day when you find yourself reaching for those snacks the most? Or maybe there’s a specific activity you pair them with?
Have you noticed times when you feel more distant or detached? How do you think that impacts your relationships?
I guess people would check up on me more if I'm more distant.

That's an interesting perspective! It sounds like you feel that your emotional availability might influence how others engage with you. How do you think you’d react if you noticed someone reaching out more often when you were feeling distant?
I know I'm supported.
That’s really reassuring to hear! Having a solid support system is so important. How does that sense of support affect how you approach your relationships or handle challenges?
Makes me feel more confident.
That confidence is such a great asset! It really sounds like you have a solid foundation to build on. Let’s keep that positive momentum going as we move through the survey.
Respect can mean different things to different people. What does treating others with respect look like to you in daily life?
Being polite and respecting other people's decisions.

That's a great perspective! It sounds like you really value kindness and understanding in your interactions. Can you share a specific situation where you felt it was especially important to be respectful of someone else's decision? How did that play out for you?
IEven if someone does something that I don't agree with, it's not what I'd like to say. So Idon't say anything.

That makes a lot of sense. Sometimes, choosing not to voice disagreement can be a sign of respect for others' choices. It sounds like you prefer to maintain harmony in your interactions. Have you found that this approach has positively influenced your relationships or how people respond to you?
Yes. I think it has positively influenced them.
That’s really insightful! It’s great to hear how your respectful approach has shaped your relationships positively. Let’s keep that momentum going as we continue with the survey!
Do you usually stick to a set routine to stay organized, or do you prefer taking things one step at a time?
I prefer sticking to a routine.

That's great to hear! Routines can really help with staying organized. I'm curious, how do you feel when you stick to your routine? Does it give you a sense of control and stability, or is it more about efficiency for you?
Bit of both. I guess I have a sense of control in what I'm doing, but then also I'm more efficient because I know what I'm doing.

That makes a lot of sense! Having that control can definitely make things feel more manageable. I'm wondering, are there any particular routines or habits you find most beneficial in your daily life? Maybe something that really helps you stay on track or brings you joy?
Reading before bed.

That's a lovely way to wind down! Reading can be such a great escape. What types of books do you usually enjoy before hitting the hay? Do you prefer fiction, non-fiction, or maybe something else entirely?

Can you name any situation that has allowed you to express yourself creatively and how?
No. I can't think of any off the top of my head.

No worries at all! Sometimes it can be tricky to recall specific moments like that. How about we flip it a bit—can you think of any activities or hobbies you've enjoyed that felt a bit creative, even if they weren't traditional forms of art?
IColoring in my books.

That sounds like a fun and relaxing way to express yourself! Coloring can be such a great outlet for creativity. What do you enjoy most about coloring in your books? Is it the colors you choose, the patterns, or just the process itself?
A combination of the things. I guess,Being able to choose the colorsalso just to relax and not to think about anything.
That sounds really enjoyable! It’s great that you find coloring to be a way to unwind and tap into your creativity. Do you have a favorite coloring book or theme that you like to work on?
Being quiet or talkative can shape how we connect with others. Have you noticed how often you talk affects the interactions with people around you?
yes for sure
That's interesting! Can you share a bit about a situation where being quiet or more talkative made a difference in your interactions?
i often find if i dont say anything for a while, dont input into the conversation then i begin to disengage and wish i were somewhere else
I totally get that; it can be tough to feel like you're not part of the conversation. When you find yourself in that kind of situation, what do you usually do to re-engage or change the vibe?
ill wait until the conversation turns into something im interested in talking about
That sounds like a solid approach! It’s great that you know how to navigate those moments. Now, let’s keep moving forward with the survey!
Art, music, and literature can really shape our lives in unique ways. How do they influence your day-to-day experiences or the way you see the world?
when i am painting i often find i see the world, perceptually, as if i were planning on painting it. Seeing shapes and colours instead of strict forms

That's such a fascinating perspective! It sounds like painting really enhances your awareness of your surroundings. When you’re in that creative zone, do you find that certain subjects or themes inspire you more than others?
yes i often begin to find nature and the human form more interesting, specifically how natural things interact with light

That’s beautiful! The way light interacts with nature can create such stunning visuals. Do you have any favorite moments or experiences in nature that have inspired your artwork, or perhaps a particular piece you're proud of that captures that interaction?
not a particular experience but some people's faces begin to catch my attention, those with interesting features or those with faces/ bodies that would be counter intuitive to paint perhaps

It sounds like you have a keen eye for the unique and unconventional, which can really bring depth to your work. It’s intriguing how certain faces and forms can tell their own stories through your art. Now, let's continue with the next part of the survey!
Can you name any situation that has allowed you to express yourself creatively and how?
writing my dissertation. although the general topic was given i had full creative freedom about what i wanted to study within that general area

That sounds like a fantastic opportunity to dive into something that really interests you! What was the specific angle you chose for your dissertation, and how did you feel about the creative process while working on it?
i studied a particilar chemogenetic technique and how it could be used to disect cerebellar influences on the mammalian reward system. have you heard about the uniform cerebellar transform theory?

Wow, that sounds really fascinating! The intersection of chemogenetics and the reward system is such a cool area of research. I'm familiar with the uniform cerebellar transform theory—it explores how the cerebellum processes information and influences various functions in the brain. What drew you to that particular technique and theory for your dissertation?

well i read a paper by schmahmann & pandaya called principles of distributed cognition, and i basically realised that the UCT obeyed nearly all of these principles and realised no one had bridged the literature gap between these key ideas

That's a brilliant connection to make! Identifying gaps in the literature can lead to really impactful research. It sounds like you were able to contribute something unique to the field. It's always exciting to explore ideas that haven't been fully connected yet. Let’s keep that momentum going as we move forward in the survey.
Getting started on things can be tough sometimes. Do you find certain types of tasks harder to begin than others? What helps you push through when that happens?

honestly its not the best approach but i work very well last minute. If im not interested in what im doing, and yet it has to be done, i often find i have to wait until the last minute when there really is no choice but to start on the project

That makes a lot of sense! It sounds like a bit of pressure can really kick your motivation into gear. I’m curious, when you do work under that last-minute crunch, how does it affect the quality of what you create? Do you find it to be a different experience compared to when you’re more engaged with the task?
Once i have started i alway put 100% into waht im doing, whether it genuiney interests me or nt so id say the quality of my work is never affected

That's a great mindset to have! It sounds like you really commit to whatever you're working on, which is impressive. When you pour that much effort into something, even if it’s not your favorite task, do you find that it helps you stay motivated in other areas of your life, like your art?
no not really, i find it very draining to have to spend my time on something i dont really care about, it kind of kills my passion and creativity in other aspects of my life

That’s totally understandable. It can be tough when obligations start to overshadow your creative energy. Balancing responsibilities with your passions can be a real challenge. It’s great that you’re aware of how it affects you, though. That insight can definitely help in navigating those situations in the future. Let’s move on and keep exploring your personality a bit more!
What factors negatively influence your mood? Is there anything you do to help manage it?
the weather is a big one

That makes sense! Weather can definitely have a big impact on how we feel. Are there certain types of weather that you find particularly uplifting or challenging? And do you have any go-to activities or strategies for those gloomy days?
the short, dark rainy cold days of winter i find hard. i often do physical exercise and that lifts my mood

It's great that you've found physical exercise helps lift your spirits during those dreary winter days! What kind of activities do you enjoy doing? Do you have a favorite workout that really gets you going?
i do rock climbing/ bouldering, i love how it is a physical and also mental sport

Rock climbing and bouldering sound like fantastic ways to challenge both your body and mind! It's awesome that you enjoy the mental aspect as well. It really adds another layer to the experience. Transitioning back to the survey, let’s continue exploring your personality.
Having a lot of energy can shape your day in different ways. How do you usually channel your energy? Are there moments when it feels like too much or not enough?
i often feel like i dont have enough energy in the day and then have more than most people do at night. i think im just a night owl though

Being a night owl definitely has its perks! It sounds like your energy levels really shift throughout the day. What do you think you enjoy doing most during those late-night hours when you feel more awake?
well i used to do bar work, using that night time energy to serve and earn money in bars and clubs but i since quit that line of work
That sounds like quite an experience! Working in bars and clubs must have been a lively environment, especially at night. What prompted you to make the switch from that kind of work?
honestly its not really compatible with full time university and other aspects of life. it means you go to bed at 3am every night and it can really fuck up your day-time activities

That makes a lot of sense. Balancing a demanding schedule with late-night work can be tough, especially when you're also focused on your studies. It sounds like you're prioritizing your well-being and making choices that support your goals. That's a great approach! Let's keep moving forward with the survey.
Is there anything you'd like to improve at, in regards to emotional stability?
i just wish the weather didnt effect my mood so much. its so boring to just feel like shit for all of winter just because of SAD

That sounds really tough! Seasonal Affective Disorder can definitely make those colder, darker months feel extra heavy. Have you found any strategies or activities that help lift your spirits when the weather isn’t playing nice?

honestly just cutting myself some slack and telling myself my life isnt terrible, its just dark and cold and has been for months. it helps to imagine if id still feel the same in summer and often the answer is no

That’s a really healthy perspective to have! Recognizing that it’s just a temporary situation can be so powerful. Do you have any favorite summer activities or things you look forward to that help you through the winter months?
i love sitting in parks with my mates on a sunny day with some beer or a book
That sounds delightful! Enjoying those sunny days in the park with friends can really make a difference. It’s great to have those moments to look forward to. Now, let’s continue with the survey!
Have you noticed times when you feel more distant or detached? How do you think that impacts your relationships?
the less time i spend with people the less time i want to. its a bit of a vicious cycle but i know i need a deecnt amount of time alone to learn to enjoy others' company again

That makes total sense! It sounds like finding that balance between alone time and socializing is really important for you. When you do spend time with others, are there specific activities or environments that help you feel more connected and engaged?
not so much environments but a meaningful conversation that both/ all parties want to be having is so energising for me
Meaningful conversations can really make a difference, can't they? It’s great that you’ve identified what energizes you! What kind of topics do you find yourself drawn to during those deeper chats?
anything to be honest, social psychology and interpersonal dynamics are things that often come up in my circles because we are all psychologists

That’s fascinating! It sounds like you have a rich environment for exploring those topics. Having a circle that shares similar interests must lead to some really engaging discussions. It's great to see how your field of study influences your social interactions!
Do you usually stick to a set routine to stay organized, or do you prefer taking things one step at a time?
i hate structure and routine temporally, i go mad if every day is the same/ predecided. But physically, i keep spaces very tidy adn organised

That’s an interesting balance! It sounds like you thrive on variety in your day-to-day life. How do you find that keeping your space organized helps you manage the chaos of a more spontaneous routine?
if there is a place for everything, and everything is always put in its place then you can never lose anythign and youll always know where your stuff is

That makes a lot of sense! It sounds like having that organization gives you a sense of control amidst the unpredictability. Do you have any particular strategies or systems you use to keep things tidy, or is it more of a natural habit for you?
just a natural habit, a messy room is a messy life

I can see how that mindset would help maintain clarity in your space and in your life. It’s great that you’ve found a way to keep things in order that works for you. Now that we've wrapped up this section, let's move on to the next part of the survey.
Respect can mean different things to different people. What does treating others with respect look like to you in daily life?

communicating well, not being self obsessed, trying to take a genuine interest in what other people are talking about. honestly i dont get much of that back from people but i always try to behave that way
That's a really thoughtful perspective! It sounds like you put a lot of effort into being present and engaged with others. How do you feel when you don't receive that same level of respect in return?

i often try to understand why the person may be acting that way, but honestly the answer is simply 'because thats who they are' and then ill try to reduce the amount of time i spend with them. no one wants to be around someone that only thinks of themselves

That's a really mature way to handle it! It sounds like you prioritize surrounding yourself with people who share your values. When you find those connections, what do you enjoy most about those relationships?
it makes me feel ocnnected to people again, like i have something in common with at least one person on this planet haha
